article.headline: Hofstra 84, Siena 80
article.story: Albany, N.Y. (AP) -- Carlos Rivera scored 26 points to lead Hofstra in an 84-80 win over Siena Wednesday night. Rivera scored two foul shots with 3.7 seconds left to seal the win for Hofstra (3-3). Hofstra jumped out to an early 21-10 lead and converted 8-of-13 first half 3-point attempts to take a 32-24 lead at the half. Hofstra lead for most of the second half. Siena (2-3) hung on, and pulled within four points at 78-74 with a minute to play. Loren Stokes, who scored 20 points in the game, hit a running bank shot as the shot clock was winding down with 28 seconds left to help Hofstra hold onto the lead at 80-74. Kenny Hasbrouck brought the Saints within two points on a lay-up with a few seconds left at 82-80, but Rivera's foul shots sealed the win. Edwin Ubiles scored 18 to lead Siena. The Saints outrebounded Hofstra 37-26, but Hofstra shot 55 percent from 3-point range.
